    "actions_taken": [
      "Injured party evacuated",
      "Medical examination on 10-Feb-2014",
      "Surgery performed on 28-Feb-2014"
    ],
    "summary": "On 06-Feb-2014 at 1900 hours, the Field Foreman at BA A133 platform 'B' attempted to move a swiveling 1\" drain line below the surge separator. The foreman's right bicep detached, balling up toward his right shoulder. The injured party was evacuated and diagnosed with a torn ligament. Investigation determined the injury was caused by pre-existing tendon deterioration unknown to the worker, not by unsafe practices or equipment.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Routine physical examinations or stretching may have prevented or delayed this injury"
    ],
